  <header class="article-header">
    <h1 title="How is Belvo different? " class="article-title">
      How is Belvo different? 
      
    </h1>

    <div class="article-author">
      
      <div class="article-meta">
        

        <ul class="meta-group">
          
            <li class="meta-data"><time datetime="2021-11-08T17:21:35Z" title="2021-11-08 11:21" data-datetime="relative">1 year ago</time></li>
            <li class="meta-data">Updated</li>
          
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    
      <a class="article-subscribe" rel="nofollow" role="button" aria-selected="false" data-method="post" href="/hc/en-us/articles/360005817337-How-is-Belvo-different-/subscription.html">Follow</a>
    
  </header>

  <section class="article-info">
    <div class="article-content">
      <div class="article-body"><p>Belvo is the leading Open Finance API platform in Latin America. As such we strive to be different and better in a number of ways:</p>
<ul>
<li>By providing pan-Latam coverage, supporting ambitious companies and developers as they scale and launch operations across countries.</li>
<li>By leveraging the most advanced technology. We don't make use of low-reliability solutions such as screen scraping but rather use proprietary technology to connect directly to financial institutions. This leads to a much more robust product which provides higher uptime, faster sync speeds, and less dependence on bank frontend interfaces.</li>
<li>By providing access to both bank and non-bank financial information. Our product has been specifically built for the Latin American market where many non-bank institutions hold valuable financial information. For example, our API offers access to fiscal information on individuals and businesses in Mexico.</li>
</ul>
<p>In addition, Belvo is backed by some of the leading investors in the US and Latin America, including Founders Fund, Kaszek Ventures and YCombinator.</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p></div>

